-02-03  bxf15 2020-05-21jxf15 2020-05-21 (telework)axf14 2020-08-14 telework; publisher to mail print copy week of August 10th; to ISSN follow-up waiting for hard copy foldercxf26 2021-03-11nxf26 2021-03-11 (TW situational)arjc, 2022-02-03 to USASH/SERirh23 2022-02-15 to reviewrrh25 2022-03-01 to endstagegrh08 2022-03-10 to BCCD  a  20202002080 a2692-190121  bMississippi School for Mathematics and Science, 1100 College Street MUW-1627, Columbus, MS 39701  aDLCbengerdacDLCdDLCdOCLCOdDLCdOCLCOdOCLCFdOCLCL  apccansdp00aQ1b.M78510a5002231https://id.oclc.org/worldcat/ddc/E38rcWXWBWG6GjxQx7CDpXR9pG0 aMSMS sci. j.b(Print) 0aMSMS science journalb(Print)00aMSMS science journal :bwaves of science.1 aMSMS science journal, waves of science1 aWaves of science1 aMississippi School for Mathematics and Science journal1 aMississippi School for Mathematics and Science science journal 1aColumbus, MS :bMississippi School for Mathematics and Science,c[2020]-  aAnnual  atextbtxt2rdacontent  aunmediatedbn2rdamedia  avolumebnc2rdacarrier1 aBegan with: Vol. 1, issue 1 (June 2020).0 aVol. 1, issue 1 (June 2020) ; title from cover.1 aVol. 1, issue 1 (June 2020). 0aSciencevPeriodicals. 6aSciencesvPériodiques. 7aScience.2fast0(OCoLC)fst01108176 7aPeriodicals.2fast0(OCoLC)fst014116412 aMississippi School for Mathematics and Science.08iOnline version:tMSMS science journalx2692-191Xw(DLC)  2020200209w(OCoLC)1155152035  aDLC41uhttps://themsms.org/waves-of-science/  atgibson@themsms.org03434cam a2200469 i 1983164820250607080725.8m    |o  d |      cr_|||||||||||170725s2017    nyu     o     001 0 eng    a19831648  a7bcbccorigcopd1eecipf20gy-gencatlg0 aacquireeecip bookxpolicy default  aecip ebook 2017-07-25fxd05 2019-05-07 book rec'd  a  2017035332  a9781633883703qebook  z9781633883697 (hardback)  aDLCbengerdacDLCdDLC  apcc00aPN3433.600a809.3/8762223  aSCI075000aFIC0280002bisacsh1 aBernstein, David Siegel,d1967-eauthor.10aBlockbuster science :bthe real science in science fiction /cDavid Siegel Bernstein. 1aAmherst, New York :bPrometheus Books,c2017.  a1 online resource.  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aIncludes index.  a"If you've ever wondered how much real science goes into movies like Gravity, novels like The Martian, and television shows like Doctor Who, this is the book for you.  Written by an author who is both a data scientist and a science fiction writer, this entertaining and accessible book uses popular science fiction movies, stories, and TV shows to explain the science behind popular narrative concepts like time travel, lightsabers, AI, genetic mutation, asteroids, cyborgs, black holes, alien invasion, the zombie apocalypse, and more.  What could be a more fun way to explore the world of science than through its use--accurately or fantastically--in science fiction entertainment: movies, books, and TV shows?  Learn about relativity through Orson Scott Card's Ender's Game and the movie Interstellar; black holes and wormholes in connection with Contact and Planet of the Apes; theories about the origin of life as reflected in Battlestar Galactica, Star Trek: The Next Generation, and The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy; computer science and artificial intelligence in reference to A.I. Artificial Intelligence; and much, much, more.  Written with wit, clarity, and a great sense of fun, Blockbuster Science will inspire science fiction fans to get excited about real science while also putting an engaging pop culture spin on science for any curious reader"--cProvided by publisher.  a"An entertaining introduction to basic science that uses popular science fiction movies, stories, and TV shows to introduce the reader to physics, astronomy, biology, evolution, computer science, and more"--cProvided by publisher.  aDescription based on print version record and CIP data provided by publisher. 0aScience fictionxHistory and criticism. 0aScience in literature. 0aScience fiction filmsxHistory and criticism. 0aScience in motion pictures. 0aScience fiction television programsxHistory and criticism. 0aScience in popular culture. 7aSCIENCE / Philosophy & Social Aspects.2bisacsh 7aFICTION / Science Fiction / General.2bisacsh08iPrint version:aBernstein, David Siegel, 1967- author.tBlockbuster sciencedAmherst, New York : Prometheus Books, 2017z9781633883697w(DLC)  201702198202809cas a22006491  1116657720251107122840.3780920c19729999ii mr p   ab f0   a0eng c  a   72901020 7 a0110500982DE-1017 a190011-02DE-600  a0379-45040 a0379-45041 aAU@b000000967870  a(OCoLC)4240144  bINSDOC, New Delhi-12  aUCUbengcUCUdDLCdNSTdDLCdNSTdCRLdDLCdOCLCQdNYDWHdOCLCQdHEBISdGBVCPdOCLCFdOCLCOdOCLCQdOCLdOCLCQdOCLCLdOCLCQ  apcc  aa-ii---00aZ7405.R4bC880 a016.30124/800aCurrent literature on science of science.  aNew Delhi,bCouncil of Scientific and Industrial Research.  avolumesc25 cm  atextbtxt2rdacontent  aunmediatedbn2rdamedia  avolumebnc2rdacarrier0 av. 1- Jan. 1972-  aAlso issued online.  aIssued by: National Institute of Science, Technology, and Development Studies (India), <2000->  aLatest issue consulted: Jan.-Feb. 2000. 0aResearchvAbstractsvPeriodicals. 0aResearchvBibliographyvPeriodicals. 0aEngineeringxResearchvAbstractsvPeriodicals. 0aEngineeringxResearchvBibliographyvPeriodicals. 0aScience and statevAbstractsvPeriodicals. 0aScience and statevBibliographyvPeriodicals. 7aEngineeringxResearch.2fast0(OCoLC)fst00910387 7aResearch.2fast0(OCoLC)fst01095153 7aScience and state.2fast0(OCoLC)fst01108536 7aSCIENCE AND TECHNOLOGY.2unbist 7aBIBLIOGRAPHIES.2unbist 7aAbstracts.2fast0(OCoLC)fst01423683 7aBibliographies.2fast0(OCoLC)fst01919895 7aPeriodicals.2fast0(OCoLC